-1851717670\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/cyberpunk-2077-2-2-patch-character-customization-photo-1851717670\"\u003enew update\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e for \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/cyberpunk-2077-phantom-liberty-update-review-idris-elba-1850852291\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/cyberpunk-2077-phantom-liberty-update-review-idris-elba-1850852291\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eCyberpunk 2077\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e that added customization options for your cars and character, photo mode features, and a few “surprises” the team is hoping fans will find themselves. One thing the team didn’t mention in its live stream or patch notes was that update 2.2 would also bring a quest based on \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/balatro-goty-game-awards-app-store-steam-sale-1851709617\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/balatro-goty-game-awards-app-store-steam-sale-1851709617\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eBalatro\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, 2024’s card game indie darling that is nominated for Game of the Year at \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-nominees-goty-tga-black-myth-keighley-1851701923\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-nominees-goty-tga-black-myth-keighley-1851701923\"\u003ethis year’s Game Awards\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e. If you haven’t booted up \u003cem\u003eCyberpunk \u003c/em\u003esince the update but are curious about how to see this unexpected crossover, we’ve got the rundown on where to go in Night City to start the quest. - Kenneth Shepard \u00